helpdesk-ticket.subject: FW: Outlook
helpdesk-ticket.description:
See below.
Carole Kasprzycki 414-277-7452
From: Jorgensen, Dr. Ron Sent: Friday, November 20, 2015 2:26 PM To: Kasprzycki, Carole Subject: Outlook
Carole:
I had to change my password this morning and after shutting off my computer I now do not have access to Outlook. (I'm using Office365 right now.) Can you please contact I.T. and see if there is something else I have to do to access Outlook after changing my password? This is really frustrating.
Thanks.
--- Ron
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
See below.
 
Carole Kasprzycki
414-277-7452
 
From: Jorgensen, Dr. Ron
Sent: Friday, November 20, 2015 2:26 PM
To: Kasprzycki, Carole
Subject: Outlook
 
Carole:
 
I had to change my password this morning and after shutting off my computer I now do not have access to Outlook.  (I'm using Office365 right now.)  Can you please contact I.T. and see if there is something else I have to do to access Outlook after changing my password?  This is really frustrating.
 
Thanks.
 
--- Ron

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Carole Kasprzycki, Yes, there is one additional step after changing passwords. Credential Manager must be cleared of any Outlook passwords. This is accomplished by:
click the start button type credential manager into the box click the control panel option called Credential Manager in the generic credential section click anything with Outlook select remove from vault. close Credential Manager reopen Outlook Enter new password into dialog box done!
Peter Pfister Help Desk Coordinator 414.277.7202
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Carole Kasprzycki,
Yes, there is one additional step after changing passwords.  Credential Manager must be cleared of any Outlook passwords.  This is accomplished by:

click the start button
type credential manager into the box
click the control panel option called Credential Manager
in the generic credential section click anything with Outlook
select remove from vault.
close Credential Manager
reopen Outlook
Enter new password into dialog box
done!

Peter Pfister
Help Desk Coordinator
414.277.7202

helpdesk-ticket.description:
I received the following email regarding my voicemail. Receiving it, I attempted to log on. However, when I try to go to ciscovoicemail.msoe.edu, I am unable to find the server and receive the following error message:
[cid:image001.png@01D123E8.1DBA0490]
Dr. Walter Schilling
Associate Professor, Milwaukee School of Engineering
EECS Department
schilling@msoe.edu
-----Original Message----- From: Cisco Unity Connection Messaging System [mailto:unityconnection@ucon01.msoe.edu] Sent: Friday, November 20, 2015 11:00 PM To: Schilling, Dr. Walter <schilling@msoe.edu> Subject: Voicemail Mailbox Quota Warning Importance: High
Your voice mailbox has exceeded the quota warning threshold specified by your administrator.
Current Usage: 12.09 MB
Quota Warning Threshold: 11.44 MB
Quota Size Limit: 14.06 MB
Please reduce your voice mailbox size by deleting few items from your mailbox. The best way to do this is as follows:
1. Go to ciscovoicemail.msoe.edu in chrome
2. Click “advanced” and then “proceed to ucon…….”
3. Log in using your standard msoe domain credentials and your password.
4. Click web inbox
5. Select and delete all, or the majority, of the messages in your inbox, this will be a number of pages.
6. Then click the “deleted” button near the top left to see the deleted folder.
7. Then click “empty deleted items” in the upper right of the white window.
8. Give it a minute and it should clear up space.
9. You can dial *XXXX , where XXXX is your extension, and it will put you right into your voicemail so you can leave yourself a message to see for sure if it comes through.
If problems persist or you have issues logging into the web page, please call the helpdesk at 7288.

Dr. Schilling,
I'd added a note regarding this, and it's now missing.
To summarize the note I thought I added:
ciscovoicemail.msoe.edu is a redirect URL that is sent to a webserver here on campus, and then redirected to the proper site and path. During our issues with the Dell bladeserver, redirect was on a blade that was failing. We were able to move it to a prioritized blade and it should be functioning normally.
ciscovoicemail.msoe.edu does resolve outside of the MSOE environment.

I've cleared my history/cache a couple of times and it just keeps happening.
Help? Thanks!

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi again, Larry,
I received your message about the difficulty downloading the video recording from WebEX. There is a possibility that the network issues we've been having at MSOE are preventing the full download. IT is working diligently to get everything working correctly as soon as possible. As for the file type: it is a WebEx Advanced Recording Format (.arf). You will probably need to download the application to play it on your computer. Students can also download. It is included in the license.
You can try this link: https://meeting.msoe.edu/orion/downloads?siteurl=meeting
Otherwise, it is available as well by going to the "downloads" tab in WebEx. I can certainly meet you if you would like some assistance.
I hope this is helpful. Have a great day!

I received your message about the difficulty downloading the video recording from WebEX.  There is a possibility that the network issues we've been having at MSOE are preventing the full download.  IT is working diligently to get everything working correctly as soon as possible.  As for the file type: it is a WebEx Advanced Recording Format (.arf).  You will probably need to download the application to play it on your computer.  Students can also download.  It is included in the license.

You can try this link: https://meeting.msoe.edu/orion/downloads?siteurl=meeting

Otherwise, it is available as well by going to the "downloads" tab in WebEx.  I can certainly meet you if you would like some assistance.

I hope this is helpful.  Have a great day!

Andrew M. Holmes, M.Ed
Instructional Technology Technician

phone:  x6765

helpdesk-note.body: I went over to S344 and have looked at the following computers: Bench 1: Network, Domain working normally. Bench 2: SMART reports imminent failure. Verified using crystaldiskinfo to read SMART errors, high number of reallocated sectors. Disk needs to be replaced ASAP. Checked networking, no issues pinging or loading web pages. Unable to log in using domain credentials, removed and readded to domain, resolving the login issues. Bench 4: Checked networking, no issues pinging or loading web pages. Unable to log in using domain credentials, removed and readded to domain, resolving the login issues. Bench 5: Machine does not power on. Verified that the outlet the computer was plugged into was working. Unable to do any further troubleshooting due to lock on machine, EECS said that the person who has the key had left for the day. Bench 7: Network, Domain working normally. Bench 8: Network, Domain working normally. All other computers were in use by students. After discussing the room with Peter, I am planning on talking to proffesors who use the room in order to try and pinpoint all the issues so they can be resolved. I have classes with Weier and Trawicki so I will probably primarily be asking them about the issues.

helpdesk-note.body:
Bench 2: I have replaced the hard drive in the desktop using a laptop drive from the box of laptop hard drive that Cameron pointed me to. The old disk was cloned to the new one. I verified that the system was working properly after the swap. All issues should be eliminated from this machine now.
The only computer that still has issues (as far as I am aware) is number 5. I tested the PSU in the machine by swapping it to another computer, which proceeded to power on with the PSU. This leads me to believe that the issue may have either deeper or shallower roots. It is possible that the button on the front of the case is not working properly, however, it is also possible that the motherboard itself has pooped out. This computer will likely need to be brought back to the desk for further investigation.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: E-mail "Contact Card" Anomaly
helpdesk-ticket.description:
IT and Registrar Staff:
I just noticed an anomaly with one of the BE student's e-mail contact cards (the information you see when you left click on an e-mail address). The student in question is Daniel Filler (fillerd@msoe.edu<mailto:fillerd@msoe.edu>). His card shows him as an ME student. Note that I checked the BE-Students mailing list and found he is on it. Being on the mailing list is actually more important than the major listed on his contact card. However, I'd still like you to investigate this to determine how it was his major was incorrectly listed and more important if this mistake is messing up anything more important.
Dr. Tritt
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
IT and Registrar Staff:
 
I just noticed an anomaly with one of the BE student’s e-mail contact cards (the information you see when you left click on an e-mail address). The student in question is Daniel Filler (fillerd@msoe.edu). His card shows him as an ME student. Note that I checked the BE-Students mailing list and found he is on it. Being on the mailing list is actually more important than the major listed on his contact card. However, I’d still like you to investigate this to determine how it was his major was incorrectly listed and more important if this mistake is messing up anything more important.
 
Dr. Tritt

helpdesk-note.body:
Hello Dr Tritt.
The account provisioning tool we used to use called loginman assigned that designation in his outlook card. We no longer make that distinction with our new account provisioning tool called FIM. According to the system admin, this designation doesn't affect any access in any way. This is a reason we were able to stop doing it. We have corrected his card in any case.
We have received a few incidents similar to this and we are concerned about mailing lists for majors but we have no real way of tracing all of that traffic. If there are any examples of emails that you have sent that didn't get to a student, the header information from that email would be very helpful.
I am going to mark this incident as resolved. Please feel free to contact me or the help desk with any additional questions.
Peter Pfister Help Desk Coordinator 414.277.7202

From: fimservice@msoe.edu [mailto:fimservice@msoe.edu] Sent: Wednesday, November 25, 2015 1:01 AM To: Schultz, Dr. Joshua Subject: Your MSOE account password is going to expire soon!
Your MSOE account password is scheduled to expire on 12/08/2015.
[MSOE Logo][Milwaukee School of Engineering]<http://www.msoe.edu>
Hello Joshua,
The password for your MSOE account (schultzj@msoe.edu<mailto:schultzj@msoe.edu>) is scheduled to expire on 12/08/2015. It is highly recommended to change the password for this account prior to 12/08/2015 to avoid any disruption in access. If you do not change the password before the expiration date, access to MSOE systems will be disabled.
Log on to the MSOE password reset portal at pwd.msoe.edu<https://pwd.msoe.edu> and reset your password using the security questions previously provided.
If you have not yet registered for the MSOE password reset portal, go to pwdreg.msoe.edu<https://pwdreg.msoe.edu> and complete the registration process prior to changing your password.
Your new password must meet the following criteria:
* Passwords must be at least 8 characters * Passwords must include at least 3 out of these 4 items: * Uppercase letter * Lowercase letter * A number * A symbol Note: The previous four passwords are remembered by the system, so you will need to use a unique password each time your password changes.
Please contact the Help Desk<http://helpdesk.msoe.edu> if you have any questions or problems resetting your password.
No MSOE employees nor any MSOE correspondence will ever ask you for your account password.​
Thank you, The MSOE Help Desk (414) 277-7288

Hi schultzj, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/3090
The school offers a vpn program call globalprotect that you can download from https://sslvpn.msoe.edu . Once you download, you should be able to enter your credentials and "connect" which will connect you to our MSOE network. A guide for the setup of globalprotect is provided at https://community.msoe.edu/thread/2059 . I will be marking this issue resolved, however, if you have any additional questions or concerns, please feel free to contact us.
Thanks,

helpdesk-ticket.description:
Something seems weird in the address master for zip 5 - at least for address types of NPR1, 2 or 3. I ran an Infomaker report for Dean's and Honors for JoEllen Burdue in Marketing. Double checking the list, I noted that Student #540736 (Ryan Kraemer) had no zip 5 in the query. He's the only one missing it. I tried taking out the address type and putting it back in. Nothing. I went to another student (#546113) and deleted her zip code. When I re-entered it, she, too, had no zip 5. Is there a job that populates zip5 that may have gotten disconnected in all the craziness?
Val

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Sarah Rowell, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/3101
I was able to print in color. There is one small detail that I believe may be the cause of your issues. Follow you printing defaults to grayscale. Below I have included the steps to set the setting to color or return it to grayscale. These are done in microsoft word, and may vary slightly if using another program to print.
1) Open the document you want to print 2) Select Print 3) Select Follow You Printing 4) Under the printer there should be blue text that says "Printer Properties" 5) A new window will pop up with a variety of tabs. You will want to select the "Quality" Tab 6) Under Select Color, you will want to change it to "Auto Color" 7) Select OK and Print your document 8) Repeat steps 4-6 however, instead of selecting "Auto Color" you will want to select "Grayscale" 9) Select OK
Please let us know if this solves your problem.
Thanks,
Thomas Schleich helpdesk@msoe.edu 414-277-7288

helpdesk-note.body:

Pat

helpdesk-note.body-html: I called and left a voicemail for Dr Durant letting him know we have escalated this to the Community Team.

helpdesk-note.body:
Dr. Eric Durant,
I apologize for the inconvenience. The type of content edit you are referring to would be related to personally created content, which is stored within your profile. The feature that enables this is currently being tested, as that is a potential for functionally conflicts. We are working to restore this.
The ability to edit, or create content within a space or group for space and group users does still exist. This is done within the "Action" menu from within a space. This then will allow you to create a document, or upload a document within that space. I have attached a screenshot of the EECS space as an example.
I understand the inconvenience of the functionalities absence.Thank you for your understanding as we work though the resolution.If there are any remaining concerns related to the issue, please let us know by responding to this case.
Regards,

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Paula Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/3140
The current services outages have slightly interrupted the print system. Card swipe authentication is intermittent and unreliable on most university printers currently. The highest chance of success for logging into a printer is by entering your username and password. Note that the process of logging in can take much longer than normal, and sometimes will time out causing a authentication failed error. We are working to resolve our server issue as quickly as possible. We appreciate your patience. If you have any questions please reply to this ticket or give us a call at x7288. Have a nice day.
Thanks, MSOE Information Technology Cameron Wilson 414-277-7288 helpdesk@msoe.edu

helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hello
Can you please read the below email and verify that this is a new process for changing our passwords?
Tara Caldwell Administrative Assistant Civil and Architectural Engineering and Construction Management Department 414-277-7301 Caldwell@msoe.edu<mailto:Caldwell@msoe.edu> http://www.msoe.edu/academics/engineering-undergraduate-programs/caecm-career-night/
From: Jackman, Dr. Deborah Sent: Wednesday, November 25, 2015 9:14 AM To: Caldwell, Tara-Joanne Cc: Wentz, Dr. Blake Subject: Fw: Your MSOE account password is going to expire soon!
Tara,
I don't remember ever being sent an email like this before in order to reset my password. I also never had to provide security questions before. I simply would hit control-alt-del to get to the screen to reset my password and that would automatically update my password and resync it to the sign in for the Hub, Bb, etc.
Could you please verify that the email shown below is not a phishing scam? Perhaps IT should send out some sort of explanation about this new procedure (assuming it is legitimate) to give us all a heads up so we can be confident that it is safe to pursue this action.
Please check into this and let me know if this is legitimate. I have until December 8 so I will do nothing until I hear back from someone in authority telling me this is not a scam.
I was hacked at home recently and I am now ultra-vigilant about such things. Sorry if I was supposed to be aware of this new protocol and just wasn't.
Deborah Jackman
________________________________ From: fimservice@msoe.edu<mailto:fimservice@msoe.edu> <fimservice@msoe.edu<mailto:fimservice@msoe.edu>> Sent: Wednesday, November 25, 2015 1:00 AM To: Jackman, Dr. Deborah Subject: Your MSOE account password is going to expire soon!
Your MSOE account password is scheduled to expire on 12/08/2015.
[MSOE Logo][Milwaukee School of Engineering]<http://www.msoe.edu>
Hello Deborah,
The password for your MSOE account (jackman@msoe.edu<mailto:jackman@msoe.edu>) is scheduled to expire on 12/08/2015. It is highly recommended to change the password for this account prior to 12/08/2015 to avoid any disruption in access. If you do not change the password before the expiration date, access to MSOE systems will be disabled.
Log on to the MSOE password reset portal at pwd.msoe.edu<https://pwd.msoe.edu> and reset your password using the security questions previously provided.
If you have not yet registered for the MSOE password reset portal, go to pwdreg.msoe.edu<https://pwdreg.msoe.edu> and complete the registration process prior to changing your password.
Your new password must meet the following criteria:
* Passwords must be at least 8 characters * Passwords must include at least 3 out of these 4 items: * Uppercase letter * Lowercase letter * A number * A symbol Note: The previous four passwords are remembered by the system, so you will need to use a unique password each time your password changes.
Please contact the Help Desk<http://helpdesk.msoe.edu> if you have any questions or problems resetting your password.
No MSOE employees nor any MSOE correspondence will ever ask you for your account password.
Thank you, The MSOE Help Desk (414) 277-7288

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Trend Micro OfficeScan
helpdesk-ticket.description: My Action Center says Trend Micro OfficeScan is out of date and I have not been able to update it.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html: My Action Center says Trend Micro OfficeScan is out of date and I have not been able to update it.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi devries,
This issue is occurring due to the server issues we are currently experiencing, as the database that Trend Micro updates against is currently not available, causing it to become out of date. We are currently working with our vendor to resolve these issues as soon as possible. Once the issues are resolved you will no longer experience the problem of Officescan being out of date.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hello,
The laptop that was given to me when I was last enrolled in 2012 does not function anymore. I was originally scheduled to graduate February of 2012 and in doing so I was given the laptop. The IT department removed all the software within the laptop. In 2013, it received water damage beyond repair. That laptop was given to me back in 2008 during my junior year at MSOE, in which I’ve already paid the technology fee for.
I still need a school laptop for my last two semesters here at MSOE. I am not looking to buy a laptop, but instead renting one out. Would it be possible to hold on to the HP 8540W until my graduation date (May 28th, 2016)? I do not mind paying the renting fee, even if we have to negotiate the price. I understand that my situation is a bit unusual, but I feel that it wouldn’t be too unlikely to make an exception under the circumstances. I am open to suggestions, but I must have a school laptop in order to pass my courses.
Please let me know if the option to rent the HP 8540W until my graduation date is acceptable, or if another course of action is needed.
Thank You,
Alonzo Macias

Regards,

helpdesk-note.body:
This is an email meant for Kevin King (Assistant Basketball Coach), but since his password expired yesterday I'm hoping that one of the other coaches might pass this along to him.
There is a ticket in IT created by Kevin, but there was no phone number given and our databases are down so we have no way of reaching him directly if his email does not work.
Anyways,
All Kevin needs to do to reset his password (even if it has already expired) is connect to the MSOE network via an Ethernet cable on an MSOE laptop (or any laptop on the domain) that he has an account on and hit CTRL+ALT+DELETE ----> Change a Password. This will change all MSOE passwords.
However, since he may not have an MSOE laptop or have an account on one, what he needs to do is come to the MSOE Helpdesk (CC 3rd floor) and present a picture ID so that we can reset his password, and give the new password to him.
Thanks and have a great day!
helpdesk-note.body-html:
This is an email meant for Kevin King (Assistant Basketball Coach), but since his password expired yesterday I'm hoping that one of the other coaches might pass this along to him.

Anyways,

All Kevin needs to do to reset his password (even if it has already expired) is connect to the MSOE network via an Ethernet cable on an MSOE laptop (or any laptop on the domain) that he has an account on and hit CTRL+ALT+DELETE ----> Change a Password. This will change all MSOE passwords. 

However, since he may not have an MSOE laptop or have an account on one, what he needs to do is come to the MSOE Helpdesk (CC 3rd floor) and present a picture ID so that we can reset his password, and give the new password to him. 

Thanks and have a great day!

helpdesk-ticket.subject: phones and Internet
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Greetings!
Over the break, we rearranged our office space. On Monday, we put in a request to get wired network access for the following items:
1) Telephones (at this point, only 1 telephone needs to be connected)
2) Wired access to the network for computers (1 or 2 computers)
One of the workstations that was connected to a live network connection has not been able to get wired access since yesterday. (This is a new request.)
I realize that this is the beginning of the term and there are lots of issues with Dell and that the entire campus is limping along. Could we please be notified as to the timeframe we can expect these issues to be resolved. In particular, the lack of telephone access is of concern.
Thank you for any information you can provide.
Margaret
